The paper discusses operating systems designed specifically for the IoT environment, which falls under the category of operating systems (cs.OS). It also covers aspects related to communication and networking protocols, which are relevant to the sub-categories of embedded systems (cs.EM) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses software development kits for IoT operating systems, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses resource constraints, which is relevant to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
